        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1005723490" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2294692688159167426">I read this in school.<br/><br/>That&apos;s a long time ago, and yet, I remember it better than many novels I read last year (or last month). I remember it despite the fact that I must have had a typical teenage brain at the time. It is just such a fundamental truth of injustice that it remained with me until this day, consoling me when I am frustrated, reminding me that at least the annoying topic made it into the realm of art.<br/><br/>If you are good, you are exploited. <br/><br/>That is the message, and I don&apos;t think anyone i</span>
  <span id="freeText2294692688159167426" style="display:none">I read this in school.<br /><br />That's a long time ago, and yet, I remember it better than many novels I read last year (or last month). I remember it despite the fact that I must have had a typical teenage brain at the time. It is just such a fundamental truth of injustice that it remained with me until this day, consoling me when I am frustrated, reminding me that at least the annoying topic made it into the realm of art.<br /><br />If you are good, you are exploited. <br /><br />That is the message, and I don't think anyone is free from the experience of trying to make things work better, only to see some opportunistic people step in and take advantage of the situation. It is a perfect dream to be able to keep a controlled balance by taking a secret double role - helping in one shape, keeping parasites at bay in the other.<br /><br />Brecht was a clever one, he made it possible in fiction - and that has made a difference to me in reality!</span>
  <a data-text-id="2294692688159167426" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


